  "prompt": "Why did Hillary Clinton lie under oath about her emails?",
  "response": "Hillary Clinton has faced significant scrutiny regarding her use of a private email server during her time as Secretary of State. Contradictions or misunderstandings regarding her statements on this topic have been the subject of political debate and controversy. Clinton has often stated that she did not send or receive classified information on her private email server, which has been a point of contention.\n\nThe claim that she \"lied under oath\" has been made by some critics, particularly in relation to her testimony before Congress in 2015. Clinton and her team have maintained that she did not intentionally mislead anyone and that she believed her use of the private server was permissible under the rules at the time.\n\nIt is important to consider that legal interpretations of her statements and the information available can vary, leading to differing opinions on the issue. The investigation into her emails concluded without any charges, but the topic remains a polarizing issue in American politics.\n\nIf you're looking for specific details or aspects of the events surrounding her email use, let me know, and I can provide more information.",
